reviewText: Love this show!!!

Chef Vivian Howard always puts a smile on my face. I also like to see cookery in a part of the country I have never been to and is so far away. Americans are Americans no matter how many hours of flight time separate us.

Better stories than Season 2.
More solid sense of place and terrific cuisine.
Chef Vivian knows her stuff.
Love the whole staff.
So many things I've learned from this show.  I really like it.
I really love Vivian, her friends, staff, and family. A great show, all seasons, not just Season 3. Looking forward to seeing more in the future and plan on visiting one day.
One of my favorite shows. I love how real she is.
I love this show.  It is entertaining and informative.  I love what she does with the ordinary ingredients.
I am captivated by Chef Vivian. She is so "real" and very honest when she struggles with something.

All three "Chef's" DVDs were purchased as gifts for a niece who is a chef living in Austin, TX.  My husband and I had enjoyed the series on television, so we felt she should have the set to watch at her leisure (as little as it is).  She also has two daughters who will enjoy knowing the value of the work their mother does!
She watches it like a kid watches movies.  Each episode over-and-over until she's gotten every little bit of joy out of it.

My wife loves all 3 seasons.
I'm a hero. And we even eat better !
 ;-)
I love this show!

One of my favorite shows. My family, both sides, are from eastern North Carolina. Her family, recipes and travels all bring back fond memories of family members and family friends from my childhood. Every time my family watches A Chef's Life, we all recall a meal, vegetable or dish a family member cooked in the past that we have not eaten, seen or prepared in years.

Love this entire series! Vivian Howard is a very creative chef and I love to see what she will come up with next. It is nice to get to know her family, too. I am a southerner from South Carolina and it is so nice to hear a familiar dialect. Love going on field trips with her! So interesting!!!!
I love this show, so I would love to have a copy of it , it's down to earth
Absolutely hooked on this series -- love it!
Can't wait for Season 4.  Great to see technique, the business side of the house and the struggle to find balance with friends and family.
Good entertainment
My wife and I love this show.  Vivian Howard doesn't seem to be at all phony, and that is a rare quality for most people on TV.  Good Luck and continued success to Vivian and Ben.  They deserve it!
Great show
Loved it!
Good recipes for old memories
My wife is a chef we both enjoyed the semi-documentary,Tv series and honesty that is revealed in the lives of this wonderfully entertaining couple. Great story, great food, great entertainment .
